I like that this outlet is spacious and the male barista who's usually there is very friendly and chirpy. Food and drinks are standard Starbucks fare. However, as a person who has the ick for lizards, this place can be quite a nightmare. The few times I have been to this outlet, I've been greeted by a huge one at the table near the windows. In broad daylight too. At lunch today, it was rather busy, so I had to sit at the corner at the long table facing the wall and the amount of lizard droppings there was unbelievable. I almost gagged. Either nobody has been cleaning this up or the lizards are dropping it like it's hot faster than they can clean. Very unhygienic. I highly recommend the management to look into taking care of this problem. Honestly, this is the one thing which would prevent me from getting my cuppa there. No lizards please.
the waiter was very friendly and fast. The service is impressive. the place is relatively quiet so it is suitable for working from a cafe
